title: $:/plugins/rimir/msg-import/changelog
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.1.7 |2026-05-14 |''Now imports both Outlook `.msg` AND RFC 5322 `.eml` files'' ‚Äî same pipeline, same output shape. The pipeline tiddler's `match` list now contains both `application/vnd.ms-outlook` and `message/rfc822`; a new `cascade/eml.tid` dispatches the `.eml` parent tiddler to the existing `body/msg` template (so the parent shows its thumbnail and click-to-expand renders the `.email` artifact inline, identical to the `.msg` flow). `scripts/extract.py` grows a `_detect_format()` helper that switches on filename extension, plus a `parse_eml()` / `_EmlMsg` / `_EmlAttachment` triad that projects Python's stdlib `email.message.EmailMessage` through the subset of the `extract-msg` API that `run_body` / `run_attachments` / `render_thumbnail` use (`subject` / `sender` / `senderName` / `to` / `cc` / `bcc` / `date` / `parsedDate` / `messageId` / `inReplyTo` / `htmlBody` / `html` / `body` / `attachments[]` with `.cid` / `.longFilename` / `.shortFilename` / `.displayName` / `.data`). No extra pip install ‚Äî the `.eml` path is stdlib-only; `extract-msg` is only imported lazily for `.msg`. ''Inline image gotcha'': Python's `iter_attachments()` skips parts inside `multipart/related` (they're treated as part of the body group), so the parser walks the whole part-tree via `walk()` and explicitly excludes the parts returned by `get_body(...)` ‚Äî that surfaces inline images with `Content-ID` so the existing cid: rewriting still works. ''Bad Date: header tolerated'' ‚Äî `parsedate_to_datetime` failures degrade to `date=None` instead of crashing parsing. Pairs with file-upload ‚â• 0.1.24 which adds `message/rfc822` to the MIME allow-list and routes it to the `email/` subfolder. The dropzone's `.eml`‚Üí`message/rfc822` extension-sniff fallback (file-upload 0.1.20) was already in place, so Thunderbird drag-and-drop is now first-class. 17 new Python specs cover plain-text `.eml`, multipart `.eml` with inline image + PDF attachment, malformed `Date:` headers, and format detection; 4 new Jasmine specs cover `cascade/eml` (dispatches `message/rfc822` to `body/msg`, ignores other types) |
|0.1.6 |2026-05-14 |Attachments now render at the TOP of the `.email` view (not at the bottom of the `.msg` expand view). New `cascade/email.tid` is a `$:/tags/ViewTemplateBodyFilter` matching `[type[text/x-frontmattered-markdown]has[msg-subject]then[$:/plugins/rimir/msg-import/body/email]]` ‚Äî dispatches direct visits to the `.email` tiddler (e.g. via orga-apps' permalink in a new tab) to a custom body template. New `body/email.tid` renders the attachment row first, then `$transclude $mode=block` for the markdown body ‚Äî single source of truth for email rendering. `body/msg.tid`'s "full" mode now delegates to body/email instead of duplicating the layout, so the two viewing paths (clicking the .msg thumb to expand vs opening the .email in a new tab) show identical content. Attachment count is included in the section label. Fallback rendering: `_thumbnail_uri` if present ‚Üí inline `image/*` preview ‚Üí üìÑ emoji + filename. New `test-edition/tiddlywiki.info` + `test/test-email-cascade.js` (6 specs) pin the cascade filter (dispatches only when type IS frontmattered-markdown AND `msg-subject` field is present) and the attachment listing filter (only `_artifact_type[attachment]`, excludes `.summary` / `.conversion` siblings) |
|0.1.5 |2026-05-14 |`body/msg.tid` now renders the email's attachments inline at the bottom of "full" mode (Outlook-style). Each attachment tile shows a thumbnail (PDF/image ‚Äî uses `_thumbnail_uri` when present, falls back to inline image preview for images without a thumb, otherwise a üìÑ fallback) and the filename; click opens the file in a new tab. The filter `[_artifact_source<currentTiddler>_artifact_type[attachment]]` picks up exactly the `attachment`-typed artifacts of the current `.msg` ‚Äî non-attachment artifacts (`.email`, `.summary`) are excluded. Scoped CSS lives in a `<style>` block at the end of the template. Pairs with orga-apps ‚â• 0.2.63 which now hides derived artifacts from the note's outer attachment grid ‚Äî between the two, an `.msg` with three PDFs shows as a single tile on the note, click-to-open expands the email body with its three PDF tiles inline (matches what the user expects from a mail client) |
|0.1.4 |2026-05-14 |Email attachments are now ''first-class''. With file-pipeline 0.1.10's per-output MIME inference + new `rimir-file-pipeline-artifact-created` hook, each non-inline attachment becomes a properly-typed tiddler (`application/pdf`, `application/vnd.ms-outlook`, ‚Ä¶) instead of every output silently defaulting to `image/png`. The pipeline executor's nested-trigger startup picks each attachment up and re-runs its matching pipeline ‚Äî a PDF attachment gets the PDF pipeline's thumbnail + text extraction; an attached `.msg` gets its own `.email` (recursively, unbounded with cycle protection via a `seen` map of URIs). doc/architecture, doc/examples, doc/faq updated with the new tiddler tree shape + recursion semantics. Pairs with file-upload 0.1.21's transitive cascade walk (delete + rename now cover the multi-level descendants too) and its delete-confirm modal (lists the full cascade + backlinks before nuking, opt-out via `$:/config/rimir/file-upload/confirm-deletes`). No code changes in this plugin ‚Äî the fix lives in file-pipeline 0.1.10 / file-upload 0.1.21 |
|0.1.3 |2026-05-13 |Thumb rendering simplified to subject-only centred caption ‚Äî the sender/date row was unreadable at thumb size and depended on a font with umlaut coverage. New `ViewTemplateBodyFilter` cascade (`cascade/msg.tid` + `body/msg.tid`) for `application/vnd.ms-outlook` tiddlers: shows the thumbnail in default view; clicking it switches to "full" view which transcludes the sibling `<title>.email` body (markdown rendered with frontmatter fields in place). Reuses file-upload's `$:/state/file-upload/view-mode/<title>` state for consistency with PDF/image expand-to-full behaviour. Fixes the parent `.msg` tiddler's default "Trying to load external content" fallback in TW's story river |
|0.1.2 |2026-05-13 |New thumbnail pipeline step (`msg-thumb` runner-action). Renders a 200√ó200 PNG via ImageMagick `caption:` showing the email subject above sender + date ‚Äî sets `_thumbnail_uri` on the parent `.msg` tiddler. Gated by `$:/config/rimir/msg-import/thumb` (default `yes`). Sized from `$:/config/rimir/file-pipeline/thumb-resolution` (same as PDF/image thumbs). extract.py grows `--mode=thumb --input <msg> --output <png> --size <px>`. orga-apps 0.2.60 picks up the thumbnail and routes the click to the `.email` artifact |
|0.1.1 |2026-05-13 |Use `{{canonical_uri}}` (new in file-pipeline 0.1.9) for derived-file URLs instead of computing them from the filesystem path. Fixes broken inline-image refs when dropping into orga-apps (or any non-`/files/` location) ‚Äî those locations have a `uriPrefix` distinct from their `basePath`, so the filesystem-relative path was not a valid served URL. extract.py now takes `--source-uri` and derives URLs as `<dirname(source_uri)>/_derived/<basename(source_uri)>/<filename>`, percent-encoded |
|0.1.0 |2026-05-13 |Initial release: pipeline tiddler matching `application/vnd.ms-outlook`, Python extractor (`scripts/extract.py`) emitting YAML frontmatter + markdown via pandoc, attachment + inline-image extraction with cid: rewriting, executable-attachment quarantine, optional LLM summary step (off by default). Extractor handles file-pipeline's `path.resolve()` stripping the trailing slash on `output` (body mode: `--attach-dir` always treated as the destination directory; attachments mode: split into dirname + basename-prefix for scanDir match). URLs percent-encoded so tiddler titles with spaces survive CommonMark image-link parsing |
